ion names per-feature events.log only; observability.md cost-tracking quote scopes to dashboard poller, not metrics CLI.", "Added explicit research risk: 'Extending dispatch_start to agent-activity.jsonl may break the dashboard incremental-cost double-counting invariant — research must verify before recommending that path.'"], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Verified via grep across cortex_command/: ALL callers (feature_executor, retry, conflict, review_dispatch, merge_recovery, integration_recovery, brain) import dispatch_task and route their agent dispatches through it. dispatch_start is emitted only at dispatch.py:446, so editing the single emission point captures every pipeline sub-agent dispatch; the sibling-undercount risk does not apply."}, {"finding_index": 4, "rationale": "Same grep that resolves Finding 3 confirms ≥7 callers need the new skill argument plumbed through (feature_executor, retry, conflict, review_dispatch, merge_recovery, integration_recovery, brain). dispatch.py + metrics.py + ≥6 caller updates plus a vocabulary-design decision for skill-name strings clears the Complex bar regardless of how the file count was originally derived."}], "status": "ok"}
